##Number says outbreak 0229: Wuhan saw-off phase is expected to end, overseas alert upgrade

I-CAIJING

Since February 19, Wuhan new cases in the 300-500 range appeared in a 10-day long "seesaw period" , it is not difficult to imagine the severity of the war. But indicators show that this stalemate will soon end, into a smooth river phase

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Xu Jintu, data researcher at CAIJING | CAIJING Vision Center

Editor's Note: This is a guest post by Cheryl Howe

Cumulative confirmed cases: the total number of cases is expected to control around 80,000

As of 24:00 on February 28,31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps had reported 79,251 confirmed cases of new pneumonia and 427 new cases.

(2) new cases: All areas outside Wuhan have been cleaned up, and Wuhan continues to pull saws

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 2

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A total of 7 new cases (one confirmed in Beijing and 178 close contacts isolated from the 24-day-confirmed cases in Beijing) were added outside Wuhan in China, and all of them entered the sporadic phase of cleanup. The cumulative total number of new coronary cases outside Wuhan will not exceed 31,000.

Figure 3

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 4 new close contacts and suspected cases in Wuhan and other places

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Since February 19th, a 10-day "seesaw period" has appeared in the range of 300-500 cases in the Wuhan Melee, so it is not difficult to imagine the severity of the situation. But the flow and stock trends of "close contacts" and "suspected cases" in key upstream data for the same period (figure 4) show that the number of new suspected cases in Wuhan has dropped to 114, and will soon end the stalemate and enter a smooth phase. Xiao Bian no culture, but still want to shout from the heart: Wuhan hold on!

3. The continued overall improvement in the key upstream data points points to the effectiveness of the containment measures

The number of close contacts and the number of new and suspected cases continue to decline significantly throughout the country. The new suspected cases in non-hubei and non-wuhan areas of Hubei dropped to double-digit levels, indicating that the containment measures of the epidemic were fully effective.

4. The improvement in the main downstream data points to the strengthening of remedial measures

The number of people currently under treatment in the country has continued to decrease, by an average of 2,500 per day in the past week. Core medical resources have been released continuously to create conditions for concentrating efforts on the Battle of Wuhan proposed by the central leadership, and important resources have been continuously mobilized to Wuhan. The rate of severe illness has steadily decreased, especially in Wuhan. The cure rate continues to rise at a faster rate, crossing the 50% mark for the first time today and tomorrow.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 6

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Anyway, the game's up. The rest of the country is holding its breath, waiting for the Battle of Wuhan to end its hard slog as soon as possible, while keeping up the momentum of prevention and Control and picking up the slack. That day is coming. Cheer for Wuhan!

With the number of new cases overseas accelerating and the number of countries with confirmed cases continuing to expand, World Health Organization has raised the global outbreak risk level to "highest"

Summary: the total number of new cases outside of Wuhan in China tends to zero, sporadic cases have been isolated before diagnosis, the basic success of infectious disease isolation. On the other hand, the ability to cure is also increasing. Wuhan is expected to end the difficult tug of war in the near future, the overseas epidemic is still in the early stage of development.
